This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with the generation of poetry using algorithms. Additionally, it may also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it involves the use of novel elements to improve the state-of-the-art in sonnet-generation algorithms. It could also be categorized under cs.CC (Computational Complexity) as it involves the use of algorithms to generate poetry. Finally, it may also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it involves the use of machine learning techniques to generate poetry.
